kinds.name: Velocity
kinds.description: A measurement of the rate of change of spatial position (length) with respect to time.    The SI unit for velocity is meters per second (m/s)

kinds.name: Acceleration
kinds.description: A measurement of the rate of change of velocity with respect to time.   The SI unit for acceleration is meters per seconds squared (m/s²)

kinds.name: Length
kinds.description: A measurement of one dimensional spatial extent.   The SI unit for measurements of length is meters.

kinds.name: Duration
kinds.description: A measurement of elapsed time.   The SI unit for measurements of duration is seconds (s).

kinds.name: Volume
kinds.description: A measurement of three dimensional spatial extent.   The SI unit for volume is cubic meters (m³).

kinds.name: MassFlowRate
kinds.description: The rate of change of mass per unit time.   The SI unit of measure for mass flow rate is kilograms per second (kg/s).

kinds.name: ElectricCurrent
kinds.description: A measurement of the rate of change of electric charge per unit time.   The SI unit for electric current is the ampre (A).

kinds.name: LuminousIntensity
kinds.description: A measurement of the wavelength-weighted power of emitted light per unit solid angle.   The SI unit of measure for luminous intensity is the candela (cd).

kinds.name: Pressure
kinds.description: A measure of a force applied per unit area.   The SI unit for pressure is Newtons per square meter (N/m²).   The derived SI Unit of measure for pressure is Pascals (Pa).

kinds.name: MassConcentration
kinds.description: A measurement of the concentration of mass per unit volume.    The SI unit for mass concentration is kilograms per cubic meter (kg/m³).

kinds.name: ElectricCharge
kinds.description: A measurement of electric potential force per unit of electric field strength.   The SI unit for electric current is the ampre second (A s).   The derived SI unit is the coulomb (C).

kinds.name: Inductance
kinds.description: A measurement of the magnetic flux generated per unit of electric current.   The SI unit for inductance is (kg·m² /s²·A²).   The derived SI Unit of measure for capacitance is the Henry (H).

kinds.name: MolarConcentration
kinds.description: A measurement of the amount of substance per unit volume.  The SI unit for molar concentration is moles per cubic meter (mol/m³).   A derived SI unit for molar concentration is molarity (M).

kinds.name: Energy
kinds.description: A measurement of an object's capacity for doing work.   The SI unit for energy is kilogram square meters per square second (kg⋅m²/s²).   The derived SI Unit of measure for energy is the Joule (J).

kinds.name: Work
kinds.description: A measurement of an object's capacity for doing work.   The SI unit for work is kilogram square meters per square second (kg⋅m²/s²).   The derived SI Unit of measure for work is the Joule (J).

kinds.name: Entropy
kinds.description: A measurement of the rate of change of heat per unit temperature.   The SI unit for entropy is kilogram square meters per square second per degree Kelvin (kg⋅m²/s²⋅K ).

kinds.name: Momentum
kinds.description: A measurement of the product of an object's mass and velocity.   The SI unit for momentum is kg⋅m/s.

kinds.name: Voltage
kinds.description: A measurement of the electric potential (electric motor force).   The SI unit for voltage is kilogram square meters per cubic second per ampre (‎kg·m²/s³·A).   The derived SI Unit of measure for voltage is the Volt (V).

kinds.name: AmountOfSubstance
kinds.description: A measure of the number of discrete particles of a material (e.g. molecules).   The SI unit for amount of substance is the mole (mol).

kinds.name: KinematicViscosity
kinds.description: A measurement of a fluid's internal resistance to flow under gravitational forces.   The SI Unit for kinematic viscosity is square meters per second (m²/s).   The derived unit for kinematic viscosity is Stokes (St).

kinds.name: MolarFlowRate
kinds.description: The rate of change of amount of substance per unit time.   The SI unit of measure for molar flow rate is moles per second (mol/s).

kinds.name: Weight
kinds.description: A measurement of gravitational force applied to an object.

kinds.name: OutsideDiameter
kinds.description: A measurement of the distance across a the outside of a cylindrical shell.

kinds.name: Dimensionless
kinds.description: A measurement with no physical dimension.   Dimensionless measurements usually arise when taking the ratio of other measurements (e.g. mass fractions).   The SI unit for dimensionless measurements is denoted 1.

kinds.name: Diameter
kinds.description: A measurement of the distance across a circular object.

kinds.name: MassFlux
kinds.description: A measurement of the amount of mass flow per unit area.   The SI unit of measure for mass flux is kilograms per square meter per second (kg/m²	s).

kinds.name: Heat
kinds.description: A measurement of the energy of a closed system that is unavailable for performing work.   The SI unit for heat is kilogram square meters per square second (kg⋅m²/s²).   The derived SI Unit of measure for heat is the Joule (J).

kinds.name: VolumetricFlowRate
kinds.description: A measurement of the rate of change of volume per unit time.   The SI unit of measure for volumetric flow rate is cubic meters per second (m³/s).

kinds.name: DynamicViscosity
kinds.description: A measurement of the resistance of an incompressible fluid to stress.  The SI unit for dynamic viscosity is Pascal seconds (Pa⋅s).  The derived SI unit for dynamic viscosity is Poise (P).

kinds.name: Power
kinds.description: A measurement of the rate of change of Work or Energy per unit Time.   The SI unit for energy is kilogram square meters per cubic second (kg⋅m²/s³).   The derived SI Unit of measure for energy is the Watt (W).

kinds.name: Temperature
kinds.description: A measurement of the average kinetic energy contained in a collection of molecules.   The SI unit of measure for temperature is the Kelvin (K).

kinds.name: Diffusivity
kinds.description: A measurement of how fast one substance diffuses into another.   The SI unit of measure for diffusivity is square meters per second (m²/s)

kinds.name: Capacitance
kinds.description: A measurement of the stored electric charge per unit voltage.   The SI unit for capacitance is (s⁴·A²/kg·m²)   The derived SI Unit of measure for capacitance is the Farad (F = C/V).

kinds.name: Width
kinds.description: A measurement of one dimensional spatial extent in the direction perpendicular to the observer or front of the object.

kinds.name: ElectricResistance
kinds.description: A measurement of the resistance to electrical current.   The SI unit for electrical resistance is kilogram square meters per cubic second per square ampre (‎kg·m²/s³·A²)‎.   The derived SI Unit of measure for energy is the ohm (Ω).

kinds.name: ElectricalConductance
kinds.description: A measurement of how easily electrical current flows through a material.   The SI unit for electrical conductance is (‎s³·A²/kg·m²) The derived SI unit for electrical conductance is the Seimens (S = 1/Ω).

kinds.name: Permeability
kinds.description: A measure of a porous material to allow liquid to pass through it.   The SI unit of measure for permeability is square meters (m²).   The derived SI unit for permeability is the darcy (d).

kinds.name: Force
kinds.description: A measurement of the momentum transferred per unit of time.  The SI unit for measurements of force is the Newton (N).

kinds.name: Inertia
kinds.description: A measurement of an object's resistance to acceleration in the presence of an applied torque.   The SI unit for inertia is the kilogram meters squared (kg⋅m²).

kinds.name: Height
kinds.description: A measurement of one dimensional spatial extent in the direction parallel to the gravitational vector.

kinds.name: Mass
kinds.description: A measurement of an object's resistance to acceleration in the presence of an applied force.   The SI unit for mass is the kilogram (kg).

kinds.name: Area
kinds.description: A measurement of two dimensional spatial extent.   The SI unit for area is square meters (m²).

kinds.name: Torque
kinds.description: A measurement of a perpendicular force applied at a distance.   The SI unit of measure for torque is Newton meters (N⋅m).

kinds.name: MolarFlux
kinds.description: A measurement of the amount of molar flow per unit area.   The SI unit of measure for molar flux is moles per square meter per second (mol/m²s).

kinds.name: InsideDiameter
kinds.description: A measurement of the distance across the inside of a cylindrical shell.

kinds.name: FuelEfficiency
kinds.description: A measurement of the volume of fuel used per unit distance traveled.

kinds.name: Measurement
kinds.description: A measurement with no physical dimension.   Dimensionless measurements usually arise when taking the ratio of other measurements (e.g. mass fractions).   The SI unit for dimensionless measurements is denoted 1.
